When using fdisk to partition a disk, you have two partitions created for the system butstill have leftover space, also called unallocated space, on the drive. What is another nameused to refer to unallocated space?
A)  Highly available
B)  Redundant
C)  Raw device
D)  Partition forward
C
C. A raw device is one that has not been partitioned. Raw devices are sometimes used forvirtualization and also database scenarios, where the higher- layer software manages thedisk. The other options shown are not relevant to this answer. Highly available would onlytypically refer to a redundant disk or network scenario.
